                "abstract": "Â© 2015 WILEY-VCH Verlag GmbH & Co. KGaA, Weinheim.Data visualization plays a key role in high-throughput biology. It is an essential agent for data exploration allowing to shed light on data structure and patterns of interest. Visualization is also of paramount importance as a form of communicating data to a broad audience. Here, we provided a short overview of the application of the R software to the visualization of proteomics data. We present a summary of R's plotting systems and how they are used to visualize and understand raw and processed MS-based proteomics data.",
